The paper proposes a method for estimating house prices using both visual and textual features. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories, as these are the most relevant areas for incorporating visual features into a predictive model. Additionally, the use of textual data suggests that the paper may also be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the use of a neural network to estimate house prices suggests that the paper may also be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category, as neural networks are commonly used in multimedia applications.
